*Considering class assertions**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to handle testing with Class.forName. I should assert null for the codec if the class isn’t present, but the assertion will fail if the class is there. To be version-agnostic, I wonder if I could assert that the result equals Class.forName(className). However, using direct reflection in tests seems like it might be off-limits, so I need to avoid that in my approach.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Working on Jupiter parameters**\\n\\nI'm exploring the existing uses of Jupiter and whether I could add parameterization. I’m not sure about the dependencies, though. It might be simpler to avoid parameterization. I need to check if methods are package-private or public in the existing code. Okay, I could use Class<?> for a raw Class method. Additionally, I'll check if the source test package, like org_apache, is outside the library. Sounds like I need to write a file!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_VNrThm6Ob8cfRByk1K3aLgux|fc_094ee4d7bb6784a10169f9d5064dd8819fbf932f82a068119b", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/CompressionCodecNameTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_parquet.parquet_common;\n\nimport org.apache.parquet.hadoop.metadata.CompressionCodecName;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class CompressionCodecNameTest {\n    @Test\n    void hadoopCompressionCodecClassLookupUsesConfiguredClassName() {\n        CompressionCodecName codecName = CompressionCodecName.SNAPPY;\n\n        String codecClassName = codecName.getHadoopCompressionCodecClassName();\n        Class<?> codecClass = codecName.getHadoopCompressionCodecClass();\n\n        assertThat(codecClassName).isEqualTo(\"org.apache.parquet.hadoop.codec.SnappyCodec\");\n        if (codecClass != null) {\n            assertThat(codecClass.getName()).isEqualTo(codecClassName);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/CompressionCodecNameTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_apache_parquet.parquet_common;\\n\\nimport org.apache.parquet.hadoop.metadata.CompressionCodecName;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class CompressionCodecNameTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void hadoopCompressionCodecClassLookupUsesConfiguredClassName() {\\n        CompressionCodecName codecName = CompressionCodecName.SNAPPY;\\n\\n        String codecClassName = codecName.getHadoopCompressionCodecClassName();\\n        Class<?> codecClass = codecName.getHadoopCompressionCodecClass();\\n\\n        assertThat(codecClassName).isEqualTo(\\\"org.apache.parquet.hadoop.codec.SnappyCodec\\\");\\n        if (codecClass != null) {\\n            assertThat(codecClass.getName()).isEqualTo(codecClassName);\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1914, "output": 1167, "cacheRead": 9216, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 12297, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777980660222, "responseId": "resp_094ee4d7bb6784a10169f9d4f4d4e4819fadde9b3facf64004"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_VNrThm6Ob8cfRByk1K3aLgux|fc_094ee4d7bb6784a10169f9d5064dd8819fbf932f82a068119b", "toolName": "write", "co